# Leads

> This file is yours (project-owned). It is the live pipeline board.
> `/lead` captures + advances leads; `/leads` renders the board; `/qualify`
> scores against the gate. Read it top-to-bottom as a funnel. Format
> reference: `.claude/leads-rules.md`. The stages below are the default —
> your real stages live in `.claude/leads-gate.md`.

One entry per lead. Group by stage so the board reads as a funnel. Terminal
leads (`won`/`lost`) stay here — a lost lead is data. `id` is `LEAD-NNN`
monotonic, never reused. Dates absolute. `account` is the shared
`@acct-<slug>` handle that joins to every sibling business-ops module.

